Black Coffee, real name Nkosinathi Maphumulo is living proof that dreams can come true. The 43-year-old star started his DJ-ing career in 2004 when he participated in the Red  Bull Music Academy. In 2015, he won Breakthrough of the Year DJ Award in Ibiza and has performed in filled up venues around the world. To date, he has released four albums, including a live DVD and he continues to break new ground in his monumental career. The star took to his social media account to remember a prayer he once prayed to God, saying he would like his music to make people feel better. He posted a video, in which his  collaboration with US super star Usher is featured on a billboard. 